<subSubSection id="C32D599B8B4FA04388D6FC8CEC6B24B8" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B880A108B4FA04388D6FC8CEC6B24B8" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">
<emphasis id="B943D6028B4FA04388D6FC8CEC612212" box="[431,611,817,854]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Etymology</emphasis>
. Traditionally cerioidine species are named after distinguished dipterists. So. I am delighted to name this distinctive species after my former colleague, Henri Dirickx (
<number id="3DFF18378B4FA0438BB4FC30ED1F22E8" box="[717,797,909,940]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="1928.0">1928</number>
04.23 — 
<number id="3DFF18378B4FA0438AD5FC30EA3322EE" box="[940,1073,909,938]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="2013.02">2013.02</number>
.05), who recently passed on. I am only sorry that I did not do this sooner. Henri was born in Belgium, Anvers [the original home of another ﬂower fly worker, Marc De Meyer] and was trained as a civil engineer. Later he worked for the United Nations Economic Commission in Geneva and retired in 
<number id="3DFF18378B4FA0438B3CFBF9EC962525" box="[581,660,1092,1121]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="1988.0">1988</number>
. In his retirement, he worked on Afrotropical flower ﬂies. He published a detailed catalog of the species (Dirickx 
<number id="3DFF18378B4FA0438DB0FBCFEB1925D1" box="[1225,1307,1138,1173]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="1998.0">1998</number>
), summarizing the prior work on these ﬂies as well as revisions of various genera: 
<taxonomicName id="4C3771938B4FA0438C72FB22EFB025AB" authority="Dirickx 1995" authorityName="Dirickx" authorityYear="1995" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Spheginobaccha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943D6028B4FA0438C72FB22E81E2581" box="[1291,1564,1183,1221]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Spheginobaccha</emphasis>
(Dirickx 
<number id="3DFF18378B4FA043882CFB70EFA425B4" box="[341,422,1229,1264]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="1995.0">1995</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3771938B4FA04388B0FB70EDB025B5" authority="Dirickx 2001" authorityName="Dirickx" authorityYear="2001" box="[457,946,1229,1265]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Melanostoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943D6028B4FA04388B0FB70ECA825AE" box="[457,682,1229,1258]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Melanostoma</emphasis>
(Dirickx 
<number id="3DFF18378B4FA0438A2DFB70EDA725A8" box="[852,933,1229,1260]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="2001.0">2001</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
&amp; 
<taxonomicName id="4C3771938B4FA0438A97FB70EBB625B5" authority="Dirickx 2010" authorityName="Dirickx" authorityYear="2010" box="[1006,1460,1229,1265]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Allobaccha" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B943D6028B4FA0438A97FB70EAA925AE" box="[1006,1195,1229,1258]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">Allobaccha</emphasis>
(Dirickx 
<number id="3DFF18378B4FA0438C2CFB70EBAB25B5" box="[1365,1449,1229,1265]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="2010.0">2010</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Also, he published a review of fossil ﬂower ﬂies (Dirickx 
<number id="3DFF18378B4FA0438D25FB46EAAE2458" box="[1116,1196,1275,1308]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="2009.0">2009</number>
) and a couple of other papers, all of his papers on ﬂower ﬂies are listed in the reference section (Dirickx 1994, 2009; Dirickx 
<emphasis id="B943D6028B4FA0438B3FFAE1EC8C2437" box="[582,654,1366,1395]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number id="3DFF18378B4FA0438BD0FAEBECF5243C" box="[681,759,1366,1400]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="1996.0">1996</number>
; Dirickx &amp; Obrecht 
<number id="3DFF18378B4FA0438D2FFAEBEAAB2430" box="[1110,1193,1366,1396]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="2007.0">2007</number>
; Dirickx &amp; Steffan 
<number id="3DFF18378B4FA0438C84FAEAE84E2430" box="[1533,1612,1367,1396]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="1992.0">1992</number>
; Maibach 
<emphasis id="B943D6028B4FA04388D0FA34EFF224E5" box="[425,496,1412,1441]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="148">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number id="3DFF18378B4FA0438B70FA39EC5824E3" box="[521,602,1412,1447]" pageId="3" pageNumber="148" value="1995.0">1995</number>
). Finally, I and Martin Hauser are in the process of finishing a joint paper with him on Madagascar cerioidine ﬂies. Unfortunately, he passed away too soon to do more.
</paragraph>
